[thinking] **Exploring agent filter functionality**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m looking closely at how the agent filter operates. It seems to only include library code, meaning dynamic access call sites in the library are recorded but not reflection targets. It might filter the origins of user code calls instead of the metadata output. I wonder if "user-code-filter" manages conditional metadata records when the stack includes user code. Hmm, I’m not entirely sure about these dynamics, especially regarding how it handles filtering and inclusion.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Evaluating method calls**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering whether to avoid using "getInstance direct" since a direct call to static accessors might interfere with Method.invoke, but I realize the call sites have already been reached during the ActorSystem creation. So, that seems fine. However, I'm thinking that the extension load might not be completed when the typed ActorSystem starts up. I wonder if that could affect how everything works together. It's a bit tricky to navigate all these dependencies!
[thinking] 
